This paper deals with the problem of monotonicity testing, which is a fundamental problem in computer science and falls under the category of computational complexity (cs.CC). The focus is on hypergrids, which are a type of data structure commonly used in computer science and discrete mathematics, making cs.DS and cs.DM likely sub-categories. The paper also involves information theory (cs.IT) in the analysis of the lower bound. Finally, the problem of monotonicity testing can be viewed as a problem in computational geometry (cs.CG), as it involves partial orderings and coordinate-wise product partial ordering.
